@startuml CarrySprintDFDLevel1

title CarrySprint Data Flow Diagram (Level 1)

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultTextAlignment center

actor "User" as user
rectangle "Web Browser" as browser
rectangle "P1 Web Gateway Process" as p1
rectangle "P2 Application Process" as p2
database "Project SQLite\nproject_<id>.sqlite" as db

user --> browser : Select project\nEdit task\nApply carry-over
browser --> p1 : HTTP JSON request
p1 --> p2 : ZeroMQ JSON command
p2 --> db : SQL read/write

db --> p2 : rowset/result
p2 --> p1 : ZeroMQ JSON response
p1 --> browser : HTTP JSON response
browser --> user : budget-in/budget-out\nresource/calendar\nerror message

note right of p1
  P1 validates route and payload.
  P1 never accesses SQLite.
end note

note right of p2
  P2 executes domain logic.
  P2 controls transaction boundary.
end note

@enduml
